The dungeon is generated as per Assignment 1.01.
The --load and --save flags act as defined in Assignment 1.02.
Pathfinding distance maps are generated as defined by Assignment 1.03.
The Monsters move according to Assignment 1.04.

IO is done with NCurses (unless a dungeon load fails), see the assignment document for key mappings. The PC cannot tunnel, however it always spawns on top of an upwards stair (to let the PC escape in case multiple monsters spawn next to it). All PC control/interface code is in characters.c, in the pc_take_turn() function (or a function called by it. Comminucation with the main game loop is done with a game state bitfield (to request quits/reloads).